PN,40901
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F409A1781384337
OL,3,CRapist on the run after being
OL,4,Caccidentally set free from prison
OL,6,FA rapist who held his victim at
OL,7,Fknifepoint and threatened to kill her
OL,8,Fif she did not comply with his demands
OL,9,Fis on the run from justice after being
OL,10,Faccidentally set free from prison.
OL,12,FBernadin Dedic, 48, had been drinking
OL,13,Fred wine and was high on cocaine when
OL,14,Fhe pulled out a knife on the woman.
OL,16,FDedic, a businessman living in Ealing,
OL,17,Fwest London, was remanded in custody
OL,18,Flast year after facing multiple
OL,19,Fcharges.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G1/11
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,410,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F409A1781384337
OL,3,CRapist on the run after being
OL,4,Caccidentally set free from prison
OL,6,FBut in February he was mistakenly set
OL,7,Ffree from HMP Wormwood Scrubs after a
OL,8,Fcourt official wrongly told the prison
OL,9,Fthat he had been granted bail.
OL,11,FWithin hours, Dedic had left the UK on
OL,12,Fthe Eurostar and returned to his
OL,13,Fnative country of Bosnia.
OL,15,FThe defendant put forward a series of
OL,16,Freasons for not coming back to face
OL,17,Fjustice, including claims of a heart
OL,18,Fattack and a skiing accident, and he
OL,19,Fremained in Bosnia as the trial went
OL,20,Fahead this month at Isleworth Crown
OL,21,FCourt.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G2/11
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,410,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F409A1781384337
OL,3,CRapist on the run after being
OL,4,Caccidentally set free from prison
OL,6,FOn Tuesday, a jury convicted Dedic on
OL,7,Fall nine counts in his absence.
OL,9,FSubscribe for free to our weekly
OL,10,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,11,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,12,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,14,FIf he fails to return for the
OL,15,Fsentencing hearing, the UK authorities
OL,16,Fare expected to start extradition
OL,17,Fproceedings so that he can be brought
OL,18,Fto serve the inevitable lengthy jail
OL,19,Fterm.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/11
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,410,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F409A1781384337
OL,3,CRapist on the run after being
OL,4,Caccidentally set free from prison
OL,6,FProsecutor Simon Sandford told the
OL,7,Fcourt Dedic carried out the attacks at
OL,8,Fhis west London home, shortly after
OL,9,Fseparating from his partner.
OL,11,FDedic is thought to have consumed as
OL,12,Fmuch as four bottles of red wine and
OL,13,Fsnorted lines of cocaine before luring
OL,14,Fthe woman to his basement.
OL,16,F"When downstairs, she turned towards
OL,17,Fthe stairs and saw him, holding a red-
OL,18,Fhandled oriental kitchen knife", said
OL,19,Fthe prosecutor.
OL,26,@xD@AOUzD@_O]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G4/11
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,410,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F409A1781384337
OL,3,CRapist on the run after being
OL,4,Caccidentally set free from prison
OL,6,F"He stepped towards her, took hold of
OL,7,Fher and said he would kill her and
OL,8,Fthen kill himself.
OL,10,F"She was extremely frightened but
OL,11,Ftried to calm him down. He said if she
OL,12,Fscreamed, she wouldn't be heard."
OL,14,FDedic, who was represented in court
OL,15,Fhearings by a leading barrister, sent
OL,16,Fmessages saying he wanted to come back
OL,17,Fto stand trial, but claimed to be
OL,18,Fstruggling to obtain a visa.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@AOUtD@aO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G5/11
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,410,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40906
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F409A1781384337
OL,3,CRapist on the run after being
OL,4,Caccidentally set free from prison
OL,6,FHis UK passport had been seized by the
OL,7,FMetropolitan Police during the rape
OL,8,Finvestigation, but after being set
OL,9,Ffree from prison he had used his
OL,10,FBosnian passport to secure a seat on
OL,11,Fthe Eurostar.
OL,13,FEfforts were made by a senior judge,
OL,14,Fpolice officers and Border Force
OL,15,Fagents to facilitate Dedic's return to
OL,16,Fthe UK for a trial in March, but at
OL,17,Fthe eleventh hour Dedic told his
OL,18,Flawyers that he was now unable to
OL,19,Ftravel due to a knee injury said to
OL,20,Fhave been sustained in a skiing
OL,21,Faccident.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G6/11
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,410,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40907
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F409A1781384337
OL,3,CRapist on the run after being
OL,4,Caccidentally set free from prison
OL,6,FJudge Martin Edmunds KC, the Recorder
OL,7,Fof Kensington and Chelsea, reluctantly
OL,8,Fagreed to delay the trial from March
OL,9,Fto June, so that he could recover and
OL,10,Ffly to the UK.
OL,12,FBut in June, Dedic once again failed
OL,13,Fto show up to court and claimed to
OL,14,Fhave suffered a heart attack in
OL,15,FSarajevo.
OL,17,FWhen first hearing the news, Judge
OL,18,FHannah Duncan said she was "far from
OL,19,Fconvinced he has had a heart attack",
OL,20,Fbut asked for medical reports to
OL,21,Festablish the true position.
OL,26,@zD@\OU{D@dO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G7/11
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,410,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40908
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F409A1781384337
OL,3,CRapist on the run after being
OL,4,Caccidentally set free from prison
OL,6,FThe following day, with Dedic now
OL,7,Funrepresented in court after failing
OL,8,Fto pay his lawyers, the judge decided
OL,9,Fthat the trial would go ahead without
OL,10,Fthe defendant.
OL,12,FShe noted that he had only sought
OL,13,Fmedical help after telling the court
OL,14,Fthat he was suffering from chest pain,
OL,15,Ftests had revealed his heart rate was
OL,16,Fnormal, and he was discharged by the
OL,17,Fhospital.
OL,19,F"This is yet another attempt by Mr
OL,20,FDedic to obstruct, manipulate and
OL,21,Favoid justice," concluded the judge.
OL,26,@{D@AOU}D@OO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G8/11
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,410,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40909
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F409A1781384337
OL,3,CRapist on the run after being
OL,4,Caccidentally set free from prison
OL,6,FAt earlier hearings, it was revealed
OL,7,Fthat Dedic had been accidentally set
OL,8,Ffree from prison on February 6 after a
OL,9,Fcourt official mixed up digital case
OL,10,Ffiles and mistakenly recorded that he
OL,11,Fhad been granted bail.
OL,13,FThe notice of bail was then sent to
OL,14,Fthe prison, which effected Dedic's
OL,15,Frelease.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G9/11
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,410,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40910
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F409A1781384337
OL,3,CRapist on the run after being
OL,4,Caccidentally set free from prison
OL,6,FJudge Edmunds said in his ruling:
OL,7,F"Although such errors are extremely
OL,8,Frare, and indeed this is the only
OL,9,Finstance I am aware of when there has
OL,10,Fbeen an erroneous release of a
OL,11,Fprisoner held in custody to this
OL,12,Fcourt, we take this error extremely
OL,13,Fseriously.
OL,15,F"We will fully investigate how it
OL,16,Foccurred and what steps can be put in
OL,17,Fplace to prevent it occurring again."
OL,26,@oD@AOUwD@AOUyD@eO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G10/11
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,410,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40911
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F409A1781384337
OL,3,CRapist on the run after being
OL,4,Caccidentally set free from prison
OL,6,FAfter the accidental release was
OL,7,Funcovered, HM Courts and Tribunals
OL,8,FService (HMCTS) launched an
OL,9,Finvestigation and a spokesperson said:
OL,10,F"We understand the distress errors
OL,11,Fsuch as this can cause to those
OL,12,Faffected and instances like this have
OL,13,Fexposed deep-rooted issues across the
OL,14,Fbroken justice system the Government
OL,15,Finherited."
OL,26,@rD@AOUwD@KO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G11/11
